<<skillpara "LOGIC" "Trivial" "Success">>So you stay on the case. Kim catches you up on THE RELUCTANT HOUSEWIFE as the two of you head to the scene of the crime, a small apartment in a building on Faurigan Street. Just like when April Pastorak turned down your help the first time, there isn’t much information to cover.<</skillpara>>

<<skillpara "ENCYCLOPEDIA" "Trivial" "Success">>The husband was found this morning when a friend checked on him after he failed to show up for work. He was face down on the bed, covered in blood. He had been stabbed…<</skillpara>>

<<skillpara "HALF LIGHT" "Medium" "Success">>Oh god! 31 times.<</skillpara>>

<<skillpara "LOGIC" "Medium" "Success">>The fingerprints on the kitchen knife point to his wife as the killer. As does the fact that he was found dead in his marriage bed, murdered in his sleep.<</skillpara>>

<<skillpara "PERCEPTION (SIGHT)" "Trivial" "Success">>You peer at the building as you pull up in front of it, thinking you’ll be able to tell which cracked window looked in on the crime. But you can’t; the apartments with their peeling paint and moldy bricks are all the same.<</skillpara>>

<<para "KIM KITSURAGI">>The lieutenant grumbles to himself as he gets out of the motor carriage.<</para>>

