<<skillpara "ENCYCLOPEDIA" "Trivial" "Success">>The motor carriage the two of you use now is a Coupris Mark 42: not a sports vehicle by any stretch, and only loaned to you on the condition that *Kim* drives at all times.<</skillpara>>

<<para "YOU">>Still staring up at the building as you step out onto the pavement, you ask, “So the dead guy is in there?”<</para>>

<<para "KIM KITSURAGI">>The lieutenant nods. “Floor four, apartment B.”<</para>>

<<para "YOU">>“Any chance looking at the crime scene tells us where the killer went?”<</para>>

<<skillpara "EMPATHY" "Trivial" "Success">>You have trouble using her name in connection with the murder. It feels like you are dealing with two different people: the injured wife, and the cold-blooded killer.<</skillpara>>

<<skillpara "LOGIC" "Easy" "Success">>They are the same person. One led to the other.<</skillpara>>

<<para "KIM KITSURAGI">>“Probably not, but it’s our duty to conduct a survey of it anyway. Also, there might be neighbors around that we can talk to.”<</para>>

<<para "YOU">>“Right.”<</para>>

<<para "APARTMENT BUILDING">>The only stairwell winds around the outside of the tenement, serving a dual purpose as a fire escape. As you and Kim begin to ascend it, you can hear the hollow ringing of your steps reverberate along the metal.<</para>>

<<para "YOU">>“Hey, Kim?”<</para>>

<<para "KIM KITSURAGI">>“Yes?”<</para>>

<<para "YOU">>“Are you sure you’re okay?”<</para>>

<<para "KIM KITSURAGI">>The lieutenant turns to face you, one gloved hand on the rusty railing. An eyebrow twitches. “I’m fine, detective.”<</para>>

<<para "YOU">>“Yeah, but… It just rubs me the wrong way, seeing how everyone treats you. You don’t deserve that.”<</para>>

<<para "KIM KITUSRAGI">>“I don’t need to be liked. I’m here to do a job.” He turns and begins trudging up the stairs again.<</para>>

<<para "YOU">>You follow on his heels like a rejected puppy.<</para>>

